Pakistan Airlines Jet Searched in Turkey After Bomb Threat, Anatolia Says

-- B y   B e n   H o l l a n d
-- 
2011-09-07T14:59:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/pakistan-airlines-jet-searched-in-turkey-after-bomb-threat-anatolia-says.html
A Pakistan Airlines plane is being
searched by police at Istanbul’s main airport where it made an
unscheduled landing after receiving a bomb threat,  Turkey ’s
state-run Anatolia news agency reported.  The plane, en route from Islamabad to Manchester, received
the threat while in Bulgarian airspace and landed in Istanbul at
about 5 p.m. local time, Anatolia said, without saying where it
got the information. The 378 passengers were evacuated and
security forces began to search the plane for explosives, the
agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Holland at 
 bholland1@bloomberg.net  